lture that was spectacularly successful and transformative.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aAlexander III., Makedonien, König. 4aAntike. 4aPhilipp II., Makedonien, König. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAncient Courts and courtiers.  aAncient Kings and Rulers.  aAncient Macedonia.  aPhilip and Alexander of Macedon.1 aAnson, Edward M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsirvatham, Sulochana R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaynham, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosman, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Craig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeckel, Waldemar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHijmans, Steven E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Sabine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOgden, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPownall, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPownall, Frances, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRose, Thomas C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrootman, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThrue Djurslev, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrevett, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruytert